      • dSolve

        public static int dSolve(int n,
                         int nrhs,
                         double[] a,
                         double[] b)
        Solves a system of linear equations A * X = B for general matrices. It calls the LAPACK DGESV routine.
        Parameters:
        n - [in] the dimension of the matrix A (n = rows = columns of A)
        bColums - [in] the number of columns of the matrix B
        a - [io] on entry the matrix A, on exit the LU factorization of A (size = n * n)
        b - [io] on entry the matrix B, on exit the solution of the equation (size = n * bColums)
        Returns:
        the LAPACK return code

      • dLu

        public static int dLu(int n,
                      double[] a,
                      int[] pivots)
        Computes the LU factorization of a square matrix A.
        Parameters:
        n - [in] the dimension of a (n = rows = columns)
        a - [io] on entry the matrix to be factorized, on exit the LU factorization of A (size = n*n).
        pivots - [out] the pivot indices of the factorization (size = n)
        Returns:
        the LAPACK return code (0=success)

      • dSolveLu

        public static int dSolveLu(int rows,
                           int bCols,
                           double[] lu,
                           int[] pivots,
                           double[] b)
        Solves A * X = B where A is already factorized.
        Parameters:
        rows - [in] the number of rows in matrix A
        bCols - [in] the number of columns of the right side
        lu - [in] the LU factorization of matrix A (size = rows * rows)
        pivots - [in] the pivot indices (see method lu)
        b - [io] on entry the right hand side of the equation, on exit the solution of the equation (size = rows * bCols)
        Returns:
        the LAPACK return code (0=success)
